title:	nx-js-graph-plugin problem: he "data" argument must be of type string or an instance of Buffer, TypedArray, or DataView. Received undefined
state:	OPEN
author:	robertIsaac
labels:	scope: core, type: bug
comments:	4
assignees:	FrozenPandaz
projects:	
milestone:	
number:	20237
--
### Current Behavior

I can't run any nx command (including nx report) as long as `yarn.lock` exists after I upgraded from nx 16.4.3 to 16.5.5
when I delete it, even without running `yarn install` again it works fine

### Expected Behavior

everything should work

### GitHub Repo

[yarn.zip](https://github.com/nrwl/nx/files/13350557/yarn.zip)
I can't load yarn.lock directly, github give error

### Steps to Reproduce

1. nx migrate 16.5.5
2. nx report

### Nx Report

```shell
Node   : 18.16.0
   OS     : win32-x64
   yarn   : 1.22.19

   nx (global)        : 17.1.1
   nx                 : 16.5.5
   @nx/js             : 16.5.5
   @nx/jest           : 16.5.5
   @nx/linter         : 16.5.5
   @nx/workspace      : 16.5.5
   @nx/angular        : 16.5.5
   @nx/cypress        : 16.5.5
   @nx/devkit         : 16.5.5
   @nx/eslint-plugin  : 16.5.5
   @nx/plugin         : 16.5.5
   @nrwl/tao          : 16.5.5
   @nx/webpack        : 16.5.5
   nx-cloud           : 16.5.2
   typescript         : 5.1.6
   ---------------------------------------
   Community plugins:
   @compodoc/compodoc       : 1.1.18
   @ngneat/transloco        : 3.1.4
   @ngrx/component          : 16.0.1
   @ngrx/component-store    : 16.0.1
   @ngrx/effects            : 16.0.1
   @ngrx/entity             : 16.0.1
   @ngrx/router-store       : 16.0.1
   @ngrx/schematics         : 16.0.1
   @ngrx/store              : 16.0.1
   @ngrx/store-devtools     : 16.0.1
   @testing-library/angular : 11.0.2
```


### Failure Logs

```shell
>  NX   Failed to process the project graph with "nx-js-graph-plugin".

   The "data" argument must be of type string or an instance of Buffer, TypedArray, or DataView. Received undefined

   Because of the error the Nx daemon process has exited. The next Nx command is going to restart the daemon process.
   If the error persists, please run "nx reset".
```


